{"article_id":"dmVoSc9FmgAoDv7L","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"SEOUL/WASHINGTON","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"( ) -","depth":3},{"id":2,"text":"U.S. President Donald Trump said on Wednesday","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"that North Korea no longer posed a nuclear threat","depth":9},{"id":4,"text":"and his top diplomat offered a hopeful timeline for \" major disarmament , \"","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"despite skepticism at home","depth":10},{"id":6,"text":"that Pyongyang will abandon its nuclear weapons","depth":11},{"id":7,"text":"following this week ' s summit .","depth":11},{"id":8,"text":"Trump and North Korean leader Kim Jong Un issued a joint statement","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"after their historic meeting in Singapore on Tuesday","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"that reaffirmed the North ' s commitment","depth":11},{"id":11,"text":"to \" work toward complete denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula \"","depth":11},{"id":12,"text":"and gave U.S. guarantees of security to North Korea .","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"Democratic critics in the United States said","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"the agreement was short on detail","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"and the Republican president had made too many concessions to Kim ,","depth":11},{"id":16,"text":"whose country is under U.N. sanctions for its nuclear and weapons programs","depth":12},{"id":17,"text":"and is widely condemned for human rights abuses .","depth":12},{"id":18,"text":"Just over half of Americans approve of how Trump has handled North Korea ,","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"but only a quarter think","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"the summit will lead to the denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula ,","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"according to a /Ipsos opinion poll","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"released on Wednesday .","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"North Korea ' s state media hailed the summit as a success ,","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"including highlighting Trump ' s surprise announcement after the meeting","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"that the United States would stop military exercises with South Korea ,","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"which the North has long sought .","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"Despite the lack of detail in the summit agreement ,","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"Trump stressed at a news conference afterward","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"that he trusted Kim to follow through .","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"He returned to Washington early on Wednesday","depth":12},{"id":31,"text":"and hailed the meeting , the first between a sitting U.S. president and a North Korean leader , as a major win for American security .","depth":12},{"id":32,"text":"\" Everybody can now feel much safer than the day","depth":14},{"id":33,"text":"I took office , \"","depth":14},{"id":34,"text":"Trump tweeted .","depth":13},{"id":35,"text":"\" There is no longer a nuclear threat from North Korea .","depth":13},{"id":36,"text":"Meeting with Kim Jong Un was an interesting and very positive experience .","depth":14},{"id":37,"text":"North Korea has great potential for the future ! \"","depth":14},{"id":38,"text":"Kim also returned home ,","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"the North ' s official news agency said .","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"Secretary of State Mike Pompeo ,","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"who is charged by Trump with leading follow-on negotiations ,","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"said","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"the United States hoped to achieve \" major disarmament \" by North Korea within the next 2-1/2 years .","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"Democratic lawmakers pointed out","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"that North Korea had often made similar statements in the past about \" denuclearization , \"","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"all the while developing nuclear weapons and ballistic missiles","depth":13},{"id":47,"text":"that could be capable of striking the United States .","depth":13},{"id":48,"text":"\" One trip","depth":15},{"id":49,"text":"and it ' s ' mission accomplished , '","depth":15},{"id":50,"text":"Mr. President ?","depth":14},{"id":51,"text":"North Korea still has all its nuclear missiles ,","depth":15},{"id":52,"text":"and we only got a vague promise of future denuclearization from a regime","depth":16},{"id":53,"text":"that can ' t be trusted , \"","depth":16},{"id":54,"text":"said Adam Schiff , the top Democrat on the U.S. House of Representatives Intelligence Committee .","depth":14},{"id":55,"text":"\" North Korea is a real and present threat .","depth":13},{"id":56,"text":"So is a dangerously naive president , \"","depth":14},{"id":57,"text":"he wrote on Twitter .","depth":14},{"id":58,"text":"Senator Chris Van Hollen , also a Democrat , said of Trump ' s tweet","depth":13},{"id":59,"text":"about North Korea no longer presenting a threat :","depth":13},{"id":60,"text":"\" This is truly delusional . \"","depth":12},{"id":61,"text":"Trump also downplayed concerns about Kim ' s human rights record .","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"In an interview with Fox News","depth":13},{"id":63,"text":"broadcast on Wednesday ,","depth":13},{"id":64,"text":"Trump said :","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"\" A lot of other people","depth":13},{"id":66,"text":"( have ) done some really bad things .","depth":13},{"id":67,"text":"I could go through a lot of nations","depth":13},{"id":68,"text":"where a lot of bad things were done . \"","depth":13},{"id":69,"text":"The summit statement provided no details","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"on when Pyongyang would give up a nuclear weapons program","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"or how the dismantling might be verified .","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"Skeptics","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"of how much the meeting achieved","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"pointed to the North Korean leadership ' s long-held view","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"that nuclear weapons are a bulwark against what it fears","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"are U.S. plans","depth":12},{"id":77,"text":"to overthrow it","depth":13},{"id":78,"text":"and unite the Korean Peninsula .","depth":13},{"id":79,"text":"Speaking to reporters on a trip to Seoul ,","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"where he went to brief South Korean officials ,","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"Pompeo was asked","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"if he would like to accomplish major nuclear disarmament within Trump ' s current term ,","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"which ends in January 2021 .","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"He replied :","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"\" Oh yes , most definitively .","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"\" Absolutely ...","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"you used the term major , major disarmament , something like that ?","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"We ' re hopeful","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"that we can achieve that in the 2-1/2 years . \"","depth":9},{"id":90,"text":"The United States has long insisted on complete , verifiable and irreversible denuclearization by North Korea ,","depth":6},{"id":91,"text":"but in the summit statement , North Korea committed only to the \" complete denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula , \" phrasing","depth":7},{"id":92,"text":"it has used in the past .","depth":7},{"id":93,"text":"North Korea has often rejected unilateral nuclear disarmament ,","depth":7},{"id":94,"text":"instead referring to the denuclearization of the peninsula .","depth":7},{"id":95,"text":"That has always been interpreted in part as a call for the United States to remove its \" nuclear umbrella \"","depth":7},{"id":96,"text":"protecting South Korea and Japan .","depth":7},{"id":97,"text":"U.S. President Donald Trump and North Korea 's leader Kim Jong Un shake hands","depth":7},{"id":98,"text":"after signing documents during a summit at the Capella Hotel on the resort island of Sentosa , Singapore","depth":7},{"id":99,"text":"June 12 , 2018 .","depth":6},{"id":100,"text":"/Jonathan Ernst","depth":5},{"id":101,"text":"Pompeo bristled at a question","depth":7},{"id":102,"text":"about why the words \" verifiable \" and \" irreversible \" were not in the summit joint statement , in the context of denuclearization .","depth":7},{"id":103,"text":"\" It ' s in the statement .","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"You ' re just wrong about that .","depth":9},{"id":105,"text":"... Because complete encompasses verifiable and irreversible .","depth":8},{"id":106,"text":"I suppose","depth":10},{"id":107,"text":"you could argue semantics ,","depth":10},{"id":108,"text":"but let me assure you","depth":10},{"id":109,"text":"that it ' s in the document , \"","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"Pompeo said .","depth":8},{"id":111,"text":"Pressed on how the agreement would be verified ,","depth":7},{"id":112,"text":"he said :","depth":8},{"id":113,"text":"\" Of course it will .","depth":8},{"id":114,"text":"... I find that question insulting and ridiculous and frankly ludicrous . \"","depth":6},{"id":115,"text":"Despite Trump ' s assertion about the North Korean nuclear threat being over ,","depth":6},{"id":116,"text":"a senior U.S. official","depth":9},{"id":117,"text":"responsible for studying the North Korean military","depth":9},{"id":118,"text":"said","depth":8},{"id":119,"text":"the U.S. intelligence assessment of the nuclear and other military threat","depth":9},{"id":120,"text":"posed by North Korea to U.S. and allied forces and bases in Asia and the northwest Pacific","depth":9},{"id":121,"text":"remained unchanged .","depth":8},{"id":122,"text":"But the Office of the Director of National Intelligence ,","depth":8},{"id":123,"text":"which assesses threats to U.S. national security ,","depth":8},{"id":124,"text":"declined to comment on the president ' s assertion .","depth":7},{"id":125,"text":"It also declined to reaffirm a February 2018 assessment","depth":7},{"id":126,"text":"in which it said :","depth":8},{"id":127,"text":"\" North Korea will be among the most volatile and confrontational WMD","depth":10},{"id":128,"text":"( weapons of mass destruction )","depth":10},{"id":129,"text":"threats to the United States over the next year . \"","depth":9},{"id":130,"text":"In a post-summit announcement","depth":11},{"id":131,"text":"that appeared unexpected even to South Korean President Moon Jae-in ,","depth":11},{"id":132,"text":"Trump said on Tuesday","depth":10},{"id":133,"text":"the United States would stop military exercises with South Korea","depth":10},{"id":134,"text":"while North Korea negotiated on denuclearization .","depth":10},{"id":135,"text":"\" We save a fortune","depth":11},{"id":136,"text":"by not doing war games ,","depth":11},{"id":137,"text":"as long as we are negotiating in good faith","depth":11},{"id":138,"text":"- which both sides are ! \"","depth":11},{"id":139,"text":"he later wrote on Twitter .","depth":9},{"id":140,"text":"U.S. Republican Senator Lindsey Graham called the cost reasoning \" ridiculous , \"","depth":8},{"id":141,"text":"telling CNN :","depth":10},{"id":142,"text":"\" It ' s not a burden onto the American taxpayer to have a forward deployed force in South Korea . \"","depth":10},{"id":143,"text":"\" It brings stability .","depth":11},{"id":144,"text":"It ' s a warning to China","depth":12},{"id":145,"text":"that you can ' t just take over the whole region .","depth":12},{"id":146,"text":"So I reject that analysis","depth":12},{"id":147,"text":"that it costs too much ,","depth":12},{"id":148,"text":"but I do accept the proposition ,","depth":12},{"id":149,"text":"let ' s stand down","depth":14},{"id":150,"text":"( on military exercises )","depth":14},{"id":151,"text":"and see","depth":14},{"id":152,"text":"if we can find a better way here . \"","depth":14},{"id":153,"text":"The United States maintains about 28,500 soldiers in South Korea ,","depth":7},{"id":154,"text":"which remains in a technical state of war with the North","depth":8},{"id":155,"text":"after the 1950-53 Korean War ended in a truce rather than a peace treaty .","depth":8},{"id":156,"text":"There was some confusion over precisely what military exercises Trump had promised to halt .","depth":6},{"id":157,"text":"The U.S.-South Korean exercise calendar hits a high point every year with the Foal Eagle and Max Thunder drills ,","depth":8},{"id":158,"text":"which both wrapped up last month .","depth":8},{"id":159,"text":"Another major exercise is due in August .","depth":7}],"relations":[{"parent":319,"left":0,"right":318,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":318,"left":255,"right":317,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":255,"left":1,"right":254,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":254,"left":247,"right":253,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":247,"left":197,"right":246,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":197,"left":175,"right":196,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":175,"left":165,"right":174,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":165,"left":161,"right":164,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":161,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":164,"left":4,"right":163,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":163,"left":5,"right":162,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":162,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":174,"left":169,"right":173,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":169,"left":166,"right":168,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":166,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":168,"left":167,"right":12,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":167,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":173,"left":13,"right":172,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":172,"left":14,"right":171,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":171,"left":15,"right":170,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":170,"left":16,"right":17,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":196,"left":179,"right":195,"relation":"adversa